misc: armchina-npu: clarify ACPI DMA API memory-management log

On ACPI systems our safe path intentionally avoids the vendor driver's
preallocated IOVA-region manager and uses the normal DMA API instead. The
generic "driver mem management is disabled" message reads like a failure even
though this is the expected ACPI configuration.

Clarify the ACPI/DMA-API case while keeping the existing enabled/disabled
message for DT and explicit legacy-preallocation testing.

---
diff --git a/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c b/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c
--- a/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/armchina-npu/aipu_mm.c
@@ -1304,7 +1304,14 @@ int aipu_init_mm(struct aipu_memory_manager *mm, struct platform_device *p_dev,
 	if (version > AIPU_ISA_VERSION_ZHOUYI_V1 && mm->res_cnt)
 		aipu_mm_set_asid_base(mm);
 
-	dev_info(mm->dev, "driver mem management is %s\n", mm->res_cnt ? "enabled" : "disabled");
+	if (mm->has_iommu && has_acpi_companion(mm->dev) &&
+	    !aipu_acpi_prealloc_iova_regions) {
+		dev_info(mm->dev,
+			 "using DMA API allocations on ACPI; driver-internal preallocated IOVA regions are disabled\n");
+	} else {
+		dev_info(mm->dev, "driver-internal memory-region management is %s\n",
+			 mm->res_cnt ? "enabled" : "disabled");
+	}
 
 finish:
 	if (ret)
